SERVICE CLOUD
Transfer Chats

You can transfer chat sessions to other agents when a customer needs extra help with an issue, or to make room for new requests.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012
Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
Chat is enabled, set up, and included in a Salesforce console app

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

While chatting with a customer, click Transfer.
Select a transfer option from one of the menus.
Write a message for the agent receiving the chat (optional).
If the transfer is accepted, your chat and any associated records automatically close.
If it's rejected, you can try again with another recipient or transfer method.
title: Transferring Chats in Service Cloud
